2.text: Once there lived a little Red Hen. She lived with her chickens. She lived in a farm. There were also a Goose and a Duck in the farm. One day, she found a grain of wheat.
2.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Once there lived a little Red Hen. She lived with her chickens. She lived in a farm. There were also a Goose and a Duck in the farm. One day, she found a grain of wheat.</prosody></speak>

3.text: "I am going to plant the wheat. Who will help me?" she asked.
3.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>I am going to plant the wheat. Who will help me? she asked.</prosody></speak>

4.text: "Not I. I am busy," said the Goose.
4.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Not I. I am busy, said the Goose.</prosody></speak>

5.text: "Not I. I am busy," said the Duck.
5.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Not I. I am busy, said the Duck.</prosody></speak>

6.text: "I will plant, then," said the little Red Hen, and she planted the grain of wheat.
6.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>I will plant, then, said the little Red Hen, and she planted the grain of wheat.</prosody></speak>

7.text: She watered it, and it grew well. Later, she got a good harvest of wheat. "I am taking the wheat to the mill. Who will help me?" she asked.

10.text: "I will take it myself, then," said the little Red Hen, and she took the wheat to the mill.

11.text: Then she brought back the flour. "I am going to make some bread. Who will help me?" she asked.
